# Plan — MN State Park Tracker

**STATUS: READY** — Research integrated. All blockers resolved.

---

## Demo Concept

Full-stack personal state park journal and explorer. React (Vite) frontend + Flask blueprint on mw-backend. User logs in, sees a Leaflet map of all ~75 MN state parks with color-coded custom pins (visited vs. unvisited). Side panel shows a synced list view. Clicking a park opens a detail drawer: description, amenities, distance from home, and a "Log Visit" form (date, attendees, photos, memory note). Home location is set once from a settings panel (browser geolocation or lat/lng input) and persists per user.

---

## Prototype vs Full

**FULL.** Richness 10/10. Real backend required for auth, per-user data, filesystem photo storage.
No prototype fallback — all 8 acceptance criteria require live functionality.

---

## Hero Feature

**Map + List Dual View with Per-Park Visit Logging**
- Leaflet + CartoDB Voyager tiles (primary path; no Google Maps API key available)
- Custom `L.divIcon` SVG pins: filled green pine = visited, outlined gray pine = unvisited
- Side list panel: filterable (All / Visited / Unvisited), sortable by distance from home
- Map + list two-way sync: click pin -> highlight list row; click list row -> `map.flyTo()` + highlight pin
- Visit log drawer per park: date picker, attendees (tag chips or comma input), notes textarea, photo upload (mobile camera-roll `<input accept="image/*" capture="environment">`)
- Client-side image resize to max 1200px / JPEG 0.75 via `<canvas>` before upload
- Visit data stored in backend SQLite; photos on filesystem

---

## Supporting Features

**1. Park Explorer / Details**
- Every park seeded with: name, lat/lng (from MN DNR ArcGIS REST), region, acreage, key amenities, DNR URL, hand-curated description (3 sentences)
- Detail drawer shows full info for unvisited parks with "Log First Visit" CTA
- Visit history tab for visited parks (list of visits with dates, photos, notes)

**2. Home Location + Distance**
- Settings panel: set home via browser `navigator.geolocation` or manual lat/lng input (no Geocoding API needed)
- Haversine distance from home to each park computed client-side
- Distance displayed on list rows, in detail drawer, and on pin tooltip
- List sortable by distance (nearest first); home marker on map (house icon, navy)

---

## Architecture

### Frontend (Vite + React 18)

Source: `upwork-runs/mn-state-park-tracker/demo-src/`
Build output: `../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/mn-state-park-tracker/`
Base path (Vite config): `/demos/mn-state-park-tracker/`

**Key source files:**
| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `src/main.jsx` | React root, app mount |
| `src/App.jsx` | Auth gate, view router (map vs. login) |
| `src/components/MapView.jsx` | Leaflet map, custom pins, park data layer, two-way sync |
| `src/components/ParkList.jsx` | Sidebar list, filter bar, distance sort |
| `src/components/ParkDrawer.jsx` | Slide-in detail: park info + visit log tabs |
| `src/components/VisitLogForm.jsx` | Date, attendees, notes, photo upload + canvas resize |
| `src/components/AuthModal.jsx` | Login / signup forms |
| `src/components/SettingsPanel.jsx` | Home location input |
| `src/data/parks.js` | Static seed: all ~75 MN state parks (name, lat/lng, description, amenities) |
| `src/utils/haversine.js` | Distance calculator |
| `src/api/client.js` | Fetch wrapper: base URL, JWT injection, error handling |
| `src/styles/tokens.css` | Design tokens (palette, typography, spacing) |
| `src/styles/app.css` | Layout, component styles |

Dist output: `index.html` + `assets/` bundle — fits well under 12-file demo budget.

### Backend (mw-backend Flask blueprint)

Blueprint: `mn_parks_blueprint.py`, prefix `/mn-parks`

**Routes:**
| Method | Path | Auth | Purpose |
|--------|------|------|---------|
| POST | `/mn-parks/auth/register` | — | Create account, return JWT |
| POST | `/mn-parks/auth/login` | — | Verify creds, return JWT |
| GET | `/mn-parks/parks` | — | All park records (static seed or DB) |
| GET | `/mn-parks/visits` | JWT | All user visits |
| POST | `/mn-parks/visits` | JWT | Create visit (JSON: park_id, date, attendees, notes) |
| DELETE | `/mn-parks/visits/<vid>` | JWT | Remove visit |
| POST | `/mn-parks/visits/<vid>/photos` | JWT | Upload photo (multipart, after client-side resize) |
| GET | `/mn-parks/visits/<vid>/photos/<pid>` | JWT | Serve photo file |
| GET | `/mn-parks/user/home` | JWT | Get home lat/lng |
| PUT | `/mn-parks/user/home` | JWT | Set home lat/lng |

**SQLite tables (new, isolated):**
- `mn_users(id, email, password_hash, created_at)`
- `mn_visits(id, user_id, park_id, date_visited, attendees TEXT, notes TEXT, created_at)`
- `mn_photos(id, visit_id, file_path TEXT, created_at)`
- `mn_user_settings(user_id, home_lat REAL, home_lng REAL)`

**Photo storage:** Filesystem at `mw-backend/data/mn-parks-photos/<user_id>/<visit_id>/`. Flask serves via `send_file()`. DB stores relative path only.

**Seeded demo account:** `demo@mnparks.test` / `Parks2024!` (hard-coded in seed step at startup)

### Data

**Park lat/lng:** MN DNR ArcGIS REST endpoint (called server-side at seed time):
```
https://arcgis.dnr.state.mn.us/host/rest/services/Hosted/Minnesota_State_Parks_Recreation_Areas_Waysides/FeatureServer/1/query?where=1%3D1&outFields=*&returnCentroid=true&f=geojson
```
Fallback if endpoint fails at build time: fully hand-curated lat/lng array in `parks.js` (demo-builder must have both ready).

**Descriptions/amenities:** Hand-curated 3-sentence descriptions + amenity arrays for all ~75 parks, shipped as static `parks.js` in the frontend. Demo-builder writes these (researched from MN DNR park pages).

