## Requirement Traceability

| Req # | Requirement | Feature / Component | Files |
|-------|-------------|---------------------|-------|
| 1 | Interactive map + pins | MapView.jsx; Leaflet; custom L.divIcon pins | MapView.jsx, parks.js |
| 2 | List view synced with map | ParkList.jsx + context event bus | ParkList.jsx, App.jsx |
| 3 | Mark visited / persisted | VisitLogForm; POST /visits; pin color swap | VisitLogForm.jsx, client.js, blueprint |
| 4 | Photos, notes, attendees, date | VisitLogForm; canvas resize; filesystem upload | VisitLogForm.jsx, blueprint |
| 5 | Login / auth + isolation | AuthModal; JWT in localStorage; all routes scoped | AuthModal.jsx, client.js, blueprint |
| 6 | Park descriptions + exploration | ParkDrawer; seeded parks.js | ParkDrawer.jsx, parks.js |
| 7 | Home location + distance | SettingsPanel; haversine.js; /user/home; map home pin | SettingsPanel.jsx, haversine.js, blueprint |
| 8 | UX: sleek, beautiful, mobile | tokens.css; app.css; responsive layout | tokens.css, app.css |

---

## Risk Register (post-research)

| Risk | Mitigation | Status |
|------|-----------|--------|
| ArcGIS REST endpoint fails at build time | Demo-builder prepares hand-curated lat/lng fallback array | Open |
| Photo upload fails on mobile (large files) | Client-side canvas resize to 1200px / JPEG 0.75 before POST | Planned |
| Waitress default 1MB body limit | Set `max_request_body_size` in waitress call; after client resize, uploads are 150-400KB | Planned |
| Park description quality for ~75 parks | Demo-builder hand-curates from DNR park pages; 75 x 3 sentences is tractable | Open |
| Leaflet + CartoDB tiles CORS in iframe | CartoDB tiles are publicly served; no CORS issue | Resolved |

---

## handoff
- produced: final, research-integrated build plan; all 7 research questions resolved; architecture confirmed with two changes from original plan (Leaflet primary, filesystem photos)
- decisions: FULL build 10/10; Vite+React frontend; Leaflet+CartoDB Voyager (no Google Maps key); filesystem photo storage with client-side canvas resize; Playfair Display+Inter; MN official brand palette (navy+gold+cream+forest green); hand-curated park descriptions in static parks.js; ArcGIS REST for lat/lng at seed time
- next needs: demo-builder to scaffold Vite+React app, curate ~75 park records into parks.js, build Flask blueprint with filesystem photo routes, seeded demo account, and responsive split-pane UI
- risks: ArcGIS endpoint needs live test at build time (fallback JSON ready); waitress body size limit must be raised before photo upload testing; park description curation is time-intensive but tractable
